Le Monday 29 Aug 2011 à 12:19:58 (+0100), Chris Yocum a écrit :
> 
> I was wondering if we should fold "Language Extensions" into the main
> documentation?

To my understanding, "Language Extensions" refers to part of the
language that may evolve in future versions, as opposed to the core
language which is supposed to be more stable. So this distinction does
make sense. Now a few pointers in the main documentation to sections in
"Language Extensions" aren't a bad idea either.

